[3] Tennessee (hospital workers)
Date: Fri 4 Jan 2019
Source: Citizen Tribune [abridged, edited]
https://www.citizentribune.com/news/state/hepatitis-a-infection-reported-among-indian-path-staffers/article_b6a841e1-f1eb-5804-8788-8951a56ef5eb.html


A spokesperson for Ballad Health said on Thursday [3 Jan 2019] that 3 staff members at Indian Path Community Hospital in Kingsport, Tennessee have been infected with hepatitis A. Ballad Health officials became aware this week of the situation, a news release said.

"The risk of transmission is low, but out of an abundance of caution, we are providing vaccination for all team members at Indian Path," the release said. "We have been in close contact with the health department, and we are working closely with them to notify and offer vaccination to other individuals who have had contact as well."

The Tennessee Department of Health is reporting an increase of acute hepatitis A cases statewide since December 2017 as a result of an ongoing national outbreak. "While Tennessee typically averages 4-5 acute hepatitis A cases per year, since 1 Dec 2017, the state has reported 647 cases," the release says. "[Of those cases, 15] were reported in our region."

